.Dd March 29, 2024
.Dt COEXEC 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm coexec
.Nd execute a process within colocated address space
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar pid Ar command Op Ar args
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility is used to execute the binary specified by
.Ar command
within address space indicated by
.Ar pid .
Zero is a shortcut for the parent process.
The new process is run with opportunistic colocation enabled,
making its future descendants likely to be colocated as well.
.Sh EXIT STATUS
The
.Nm
utility exits 0 on success, and >0 if an error occurs.
.Sh EXAMPLES
Run
.Xr procstat 1
colocated with the current shell and display its memory map:
.Pp
.Dl Nm Ar 0 Ar procstat -v $$
.Pp
Do not colocate with any existing process, just spawn a shell
with opportunistic colocation enabled:
.Pp
.Dl Nm Ar -1 Ar sh
.Pp
